CatDescriptText: James Stark, art student, Pittsburgh, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the hospital service rendered under Blue Cross plan is worth its present cost to the subscriber? Do you think the rates should be raised?  Why?"  answer reads: "Yes, it's present cost is worth it, but I do not know about any future increases.  It is supposed to be a non-profit organization, but along the line somebody is profiting in order to force up the rates which I and others pay."
